pageContext.claim: “We're replacing one of the worst trade deals ever made by any country. You can go back as far as you want, NAFTA. The disaster of NAFTA, so whatever you do, start talking to your people, we need a vote on the USMCA, that's United States, Mexico and Canada and they've already voted.”
pageContext.analysis: Mexico has ratified the revised North American Free Trade Agreement. But contrary to Trump's claim, Canada's Parliament had not yet done so at the time of this statement.
